OL,3,CStraw flies as shin-kicking champion
OL,4,Ccrowned at ancient rural games
OL,6,FA new shin-kicking champion has been
OL,7,Fcrowned at the Cotswold Olimpick
OL,8,FGames, where bruises and flying straw
OL,9,Fare part of a sporting tradition
OL,10,Fdating back more than 400 years.
OL,12,FThe event, held on Dover's Hill near
OL,13,FChipping Campden on Friday, was
OL,14,Frevived in 1951 after first being held
OL,15,Fin 1612 when local lawyer Robert Dover
OL,16,Fis said to have wanted to channel some
OL,17,Fof the competitive traits of the local
OL,18,Fpeople.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
