OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1780315873
OL,3,CStraw flies as shin-kicking champion
OL,4,Ccrowned at ancient rural games
OL,6,FEach participant must wear trousers,
OL,7,Fwith straw available for them to
OL,8,Fcreate a layer of padding on their
OL,9,Fshins.
OL,11,FContestants hold each other by the
OL,12,Fshoulder and try to kick each other's
OL,13,Fshins and force their opponent to the
OL,14,Fground.
OL,16,FThe stickler, or referee, has to make
OL,17,Fsure that shins are kicked before a
OL,18,Ffall can count.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
